{
  "doc_id": "56",
  "text": "Apolipoprotein E genotype has been associated with late-onset, familial and sporadic Alzheimer's disease (AD) and with an earlier progression of age-associated cognitive slowing in healthy individuals [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] Roses 1996; [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . This susceptibility gene is found in three allelic variants: APOE2, APOE3 and APOE4. Inheritance of the APOE4 allele confers a gene dose-related increase in risk of clinical expression and earlier onset of AD [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] whereas APOE2 is associated with smaller risk and later onset [CITATION_9] .",
